<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0067" sponsor="Carl R. Albrecht" designation="HB" otherSponsor="Keven J. Stratton" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0579" date="12/22/2025 15:12:17" printDate="12-22 15:40" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>3</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="1" uid="C63I-1-S219_2026050620260506" fromuid="C63I-1-S219_2025050720250507" sort="63I01 02190020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">63I-1-219</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Lead Acid Battery Disposal Sunset Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Carl R. Albrecht</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: Keven J. Stratton</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><cn numlevel="1" lineno="4" slineno="0-4">Committee Note:<comrec voteid="38368" comcode="INTNAE" numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5"> The Natural Resources, Agriculture, and Environment Interim Committee recommended <ln numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6"/>this bill.<legvote numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">Legislative Vote:<yes>10 voting for</yes><no>0 voting against</no><abs>9 absent</abs></legvote></comrec></cn><gdhead lineno="8">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9">This bill addresses the regulation of lead acid battery disposal.</gd><hphead lineno="10">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">removes provisions related to lead acid battery disposal from the sunset act; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" level="1">makes technical changes.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="15">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="17">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="63I-1-219" src="code" uid="C63I-1-S219_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="63I01 02190020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20"><bold>63I-1-219</bold>, as last amended by Laws of Utah 2025, Chapters 14, 121 and 522</sn></saamd></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="21"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="0-22">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="63I-1-219" type="amend" src="code" uid="C63I-1-S219_2026050620260506" sort="63I01 02190020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="63I-1-219" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="23">Section 1. Section <bold>63I-1-219</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="24"><bold>63I-1-219<parens/>. Repeal dates: Title 19.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-3" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display>(1)</display>Title 19, Chapter 2, Air Conservation Act, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-2" dnum="2-o" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-4" level="1"><display>(2)</display>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="19-2-109.6">19-2-109.6</xref>, Plantwide applicability limitation -- Publication of guidance <ln numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-5"/>required -- Report to committee -- Rulemaking, is repealed July 1, 2026.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-3" dnum="3-o" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-6" level="1"><display>(3)</display>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="19-2-109.7">19-2-109.7</xref>, Permit by rule registration expansion study, is repealed July 1, 2026.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-4" dnum="4-o" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-7" level="1"><display>(4)</display>Title 19, Chapter 4, Safe Drinking Water Act, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-5" dnum="5-o" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-8" level="1"><display>(5)</display>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="19-4-115">19-4-115</xref>, Drinking water quality in schools and child care centers, is repealed <ln numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-9"/>July 1, 2027.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-6" dnum="6-o" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-10" level="1"><display>(6)</display>Title 19, Chapter 5, Water Quality Act, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-7" dnum="7-o" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-11" level="1"><display>(7)</display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 1, Solid and Hazardous Waste Act, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-8" dnum="8-o" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-12" level="1"><display>(8)</display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 3, Hazardous Substances Mitigation Act, is repealed July 1, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-13"/>2030.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-9" dnum="9-o" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-14" level="1"><display>(9)</display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 4, Petroleum Storage Tank Act, is repealed July 1, 2028.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-10" dnum="10-o" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-15" level="1"><display>(10)</display>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="19-6-510">19-6-510</xref>, Study of glass recycling, is repealed July 1, 2026.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-11" dnum="11-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-16" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="ahaskell" style="2" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1010" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(11)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="3" groupid="2" style="2" owner="ahaskell" level="1" deltag="end">Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 6, Lead Acid Battery Disposal, is repealed July 1, 2026.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-12" dnum="12-o:11-i" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-17" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1011" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(12)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(11)</amend></display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 7, Used Oil Management Act, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-13" dnum="13-o:12-i" numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-18" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1012" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(13)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1013" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(12)</amend></display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 8, Waste Tire Recycling Act, is repealed July 1, 2030.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-14" dnum="14-o:13-i" numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-19" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1013" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(14)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1014" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(13)</amend></display>Title 19, Chapter 6, Part 10, Mercury Switch Removal Act, is repealed July 1, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-20"/>2027.</subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="2" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="43">Section 2.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="44"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="ahaskell" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>12-22-25 3:40 PM</tm></rev></foot></leg>